		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-26022">
				<div id="div-comment-26022" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/dc5baad33fa46b71ebd378dd23f0aa64?s=45&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D45&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' />		<cite class="fn">denthyg35</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.stetted.com/index.php/2010/06/15/perfect-buttercream/comment-page-1/#comment-26022">
			June 16, 2011 at 9:29 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>I do not like a sickly sweet frosting either, so I did a little experimenting and this is what I came up with.  I add approximately 1/2 of an 8 oz package of softened cream cheese to a single recipe of frosting.  It cuts down on the sweetness, but does not taste like a &#8220;cream cheese&#8221; frosting or butter.  You can add more or not as much, depending on your preference.  I have had MANY MANY compliments on my frosting.</p>
<p class="thdrpy">[<a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="movecfm(event,26022,1,'denthyg35');">Reply</a>]</p>
